50|$|Around 1994, the top <b>wrap-around</b> <b>label</b> sticker {{began to}} appear on most CDs, {{to make it easier}} to read what each CD was from the top without having to flip through them to see the front cover. These {{stickers}} were usually nothing more than informational labels and rarely would have any use in the marketing of the album. The wrap-around sticker also provided an extra seal, possibly as another theft deterrent.|$|E

